This paper deals with natural language generation from structured data, which is a common topic in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed method involves optimizing an inverse KL divergence, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of sequence-to-sequence models, which are a popular approach in deep learning and neural networks (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves working with RDF triples, which are commonly used in information retrieval and knowledge representation (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with generating natural language descriptions of a knowledge base, which is a common task in database systems (cs.DB).
